message.content:
1. The primary composite endpoint was individual patient success.
2. The patient success was based on four components.
3. One of the components was improvement in two of three domains of the Zurich Claudication Questionnaire.
4. Another component was no reoperations at the index level.
5. Another component was no major implant/procedure-related complications.
6. The last component was no clinically significant confounding treatments.
